<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,839,1225]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,839,865]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,546,839,865]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[281,546,839,865]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Rhamphomyia caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a somewhat complicated taxonomic history. As a consequence, some distributional records of this species may be misleading. 
<taxonomicName box="[783,1041,875,901]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[783,1041,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Rhamphomyia caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified as the single species of 
<taxonomicName box="[184,305,911,937]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Empididae</taxonomicName>
from Spitsbergen (
<bibRefCitation author="Boheman, C. H." box="[528,706,911,937]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="563 - 577" refId="ref62083" refString="Boheman, C. H. (1866) Spetsbergens Insekt-fauna. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 22 (1865), 563 - 577." type="journal article" year="1866">Boheman 1866</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Holmgren, A. E." box="[721,903,911,937]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref63852" refString="Holmgren, A. E. (1869) Bidrag till kannedomen om Beeren Eilands och Spetsbergens insektfauna. Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps- Akademiens Handlingar, 8 (5), 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="1869">Holmgren 1869</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[918,1054,911,937]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="116 - 123" refId="ref62361" refString="Collin, J. E., (1923) Diptera (Orthorrhapha Brachycera and Cyclorrhapha) from Spitsbergen and Bear Island. Results of the Oxford University Expedition to Spitsbergen, 1921. - No. 22. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 11 (61), 116 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932308632830" type="journal article" year="1923">Collin 1923</bibRefCitation>
) and was reflected in 
<taxonomicName authority="Catalogues" authorityName="Catalogues" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Empididae Catalogues</taxonomicName>
and faunal checklists (
<emphasis box="[530,563,947,972]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<bibRefCitation author="Hackman, W." box="[584,756,947,973]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="93 - 98" refId="ref63726" refString="Hackman, W. (1968) Notes on the arthropod fauna of Spitsbergen, II: 11. Diptera: Empididae, Acalyptratae families and Scatophagidae. Annales Entomologici Fennici, 34, 93 - 98." type="journal article" year="1968">Hackman 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chvala, M. &amp; Wagner, R." box="[767,1087,947,973]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref62263" refString="Chvala, M. &amp; Wagner, R. (1989) Empididae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Vol. 6. Therevidae - Empididae. Elsevier Science Publishing, Amsterdam, pp. 228 - 336." type="book" year="1989">Chvála &amp; Wagner 1989: 299</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coulson, S. J. &amp; Refseth, D." box="[1098,1431,947,973]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="57 - 122" refId="ref62541" refString="Coulson, S. J. &amp; Refseth, D. (2004) The terrestrial and freshwater invertebrate fauna of Svalbard. In: Prestrud, P., Strom, H. &amp; Goldman, H. V. (Eds.), A catalog of the terrestrial and marine animals of Svalbard. Norwegian Polar Institute, Tromso, pp. 57 - 122." type="book chapter" year="2004">Coulson &amp; Refseth 2004: 104</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Zhang, K. &amp; Yao, G. &amp; Zhang, J." box="[151,395,983,1010]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref65517" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, K., Yao, G. &amp; Zhang, J. (2007) World Catalog of Empididae (Insecta: Diptera). China Agricultural University Press, Beijing, 599 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[216,265,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al</emphasis>
. 2007: 169
</bibRefCitation>
). We have examined the specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[828,949,983,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[828,845,983,1008]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[859,949,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
noted by Holmgren (housed in NHRS) and found that, actually, they belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Frey" authorityName="Frey in Lundstrom &amp; Frey" authorityYear="1913" box="[552,779,1019,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longestylata">
<emphasis box="[552,569,1019,1044]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[584,721,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">longestylata</emphasis>
Frey
</taxonomicName>
(see below). It should be noted that Collin was somewhat confused about the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[521,641,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[521,538,1055,1080]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[551,641,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He believed that 
<taxonomicName authority="Frey" authorityName="Frey in Lundstrom &amp; Frey" authorityYear="1913" box="[844,1069,1055,1081]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longestylata">
<emphasis box="[844,861,1055,1080]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[874,1011,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">longestylata</emphasis>
Frey
</taxonomicName>
was conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zetterstedt)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[1315,1332,1055,1080]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">caudata</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt)
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[346,544,1091,1117]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref62429" refString="Collin, J. E. (1961) Empididae. In: British flies. Vol. 6. University Press, Cambridge, 782 pp." type="book" year="1961">Collin, 1961: 378</bibRefCitation>
). However, they are distinctly two different species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Frey, R." box="[1167,1351,1090,1117]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="433 - 480" refId="ref63283" refString="Frey, R. (1955 a) 28. Empididae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region, 4 (4), 433 - 480, taf. 37 - 42 (Lfg. 181)." type="journal article" year="1955">Frey 1955a: 472</bibRefCitation>
; Barták &amp; Danielson 2008: 107). A note in Collin’s paper on flies collected from Spitsbergen (
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[1127,1321,1127,1154]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="116 - 123" refId="ref62361" refString="Collin, J. E., (1923) Diptera (Orthorrhapha Brachycera and Cyclorrhapha) from Spitsbergen and Bear Island. Results of the Oxford University Expedition to Spitsbergen, 1921. - No. 22. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 11 (61), 116 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932308632830" type="journal article" year="1923">Collin 1923: 116</bibRefCitation>
) indicates clearly that he in fact had in front of him a male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frey in Lundstrom &amp; Frey" authorityYear="1913" box="[761,932,1163,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longestylata">
<emphasis box="[761,778,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[795,932,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">longestylata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1198,1163,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[1075,1092,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1108,1198,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our study does not confirm the presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[423,544,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Rhamphomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis box="[423,440,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[454,544,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the Arctic islands.
</paragraph>
